## Alert Management and Response (Real-time)
**RESPOND TO ISSUES:** Automated detection and response to performance problems

### 1. Alert Classification and Prioritization
**Alert Severity Levels:**
- **Critical:** System unavailable or major functionality impacted
- **Major:** Significant performance degradation or user impact
- **Minor:** Noticeable but non-critical performance issues
- **Info:** Informational alerts for awareness and trending

**Alert Priority Matrix:**
```
Alert Response Guidelines
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Critical Alerts: Respond within 5 minutes
• System downtime or data loss
• Security breaches or compliance violations
• Complete workflow failures

Major Alerts: Respond within 1 hour
• Significant performance degradation (>50% slowdown)
• High error rates (>10% failure rate)
• Resource exhaustion warnings

Minor Alerts: Respond within 4 hours
• Moderate performance issues (20-50% slowdown)
• Increased error rates (5-10%)
• Resource usage warnings

Info Alerts: Review daily/weekly
• Performance trending changes
• Optimization opportunities
• System health improvements
```

### 2. Automated Response Actions
**Alert Response Automation:**
- **Self-Healing:** Automatic fixes for known issues
- **Scaling:** Automatic resource allocation for load increases
- **Optimization:** Automatic application of performance optimizations
- **Notification:** Automated stakeholder alerts for manual intervention

**Response Effectiveness Tracking:**
```
Automated Response Performance
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Self-Healing Success: 78% (Target: >75%) ✅
Average Resolution Time: 4.2 min (Target: <5 min) ✅
False Positive Rate: 3.1% (Target: <5%) ✅
Escalation Rate: 8.5% (Target: <10%) ✅
```

